<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><entry xmlns:functx="http://www.functx.com" xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xml:id="entry_færæz" xml:lang="os"><form xml:lang="os-x-iron" type="lemma"><orth>færæz</orth></form><form xml:lang="os-x-digor" type="dialectal"><orth>færæznæ</orth></form><sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>средство</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>means</q></cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>способ</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>method</q></cit></sense><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>возможность</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>possibility</q></cit></sense></sense><re><form type="lemma"><orth>æværæz</orth></form><sense><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>беспомощный</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>helpless</q></cit><note type="comment" xml:lang="">() </note><note type="comment" xml:lang="">() </note></sense></re><cit type="exampleGroup"><cit type="example"><quote>k˳yst — cardæn færæz</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>работа (дает) возможность жить</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>work makes it possible to live</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>55</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>æværæz synʒy kʼūtæryl bast</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>беспомощный (как бы) привязан к кусту терновника</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>a helpless man is as if he is tied to a thorn bush</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Ӕмб."/><biblScope>8</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><cit type="exampleGroup"><cit type="example"><quote>k˳yst — cardæn færæz</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>работа (дает) возможность жить</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>work makes it possible to live</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Коста"/><biblScope>55</biblScope></bibl></cit><cit type="example"><quote>æværæz synʒy kʼūtæryl bast</quote><cit type="translation" xml:lang="ru"><q>беспомощный (как бы) привязан к кусту терновника</q></cit><cit type="translation" xml:lang="en"><q>a helpless man is as if he is tied to a thorn bush</q></cit><bibl><ref target="#src_Ӕмб."/><biblScope>8</biblScope></bibl></cit></cit><etym xml:lang="ru">Отглагольное образование от <ref type="xr" target="#entry_færazyn"/> | %ifærazun%i ‘мочь’, ‘быть, в состоянии что-либо сделать’. Аналогичные образования с помощью суффикса %i-n%i | %i-næ%i более распространены в дигорском; ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xæsnæ"/> и др. (<bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">537 сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">537 ff.</biblScope></bibl>). Иронский утратил конечное %i-n%i после %iz%i, как и в некоторых других случаях; ср. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xæs"/> (из %ixæsn%i), <ref type="xr" target="#entry_qwaz"/> (из %iqwazn%i).%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>574</biblScope></bibl>.</etym><etym xml:lang="en">A deverbal derivative of <ref type="xr" target="#entry_færazyn"/> | %ifærazun%i ‘be able to’. The analogous %i-n%i | %i-næ%i derivatives are more widespread in Digor; cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xæsnæ"/> etc. (<bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope xml:lang="ru">537 сл.</biblScope><biblScope xml:lang="en">537 ff.</biblScope></bibl>). Iron has dropped the final %i-n%i after %iz%i, as in some other cases; cf. <ref type="xr" target="#entry_xæs"/> (from %ixæsn%i), <ref type="xr" target="#entry_qwaz"/> (from %iqwazn%i).%n<bibl><ref target="#ref_ОЯФ_I"/><biblScope>574</biblScope></bibl>.</etym></entry>